---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Our Story | Brooklynite Designs">
  <section class="container-shell grid gap-10 py-16 md:grid-cols-[0.85fr_1.15fr]">
    <div>
      <p class="heritage-kicker">Our story</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-editorial text-5xl font-black leading-tight text-asphalt">Established 2016. Built from before.</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-5 text-lg leading-8 text-ink/72">
      <p>Brooklynite Designs is evolving from a Brooklyn-themed shop into a premium Brooklyn heritage brand rooted in immigrant family memory, neighborhood pride, and the everyday icons that made New York feel alive.</p>
      <p>The deeper story begins with Polish immigrants arriving in New York City in the early 1990s. They built a life while watching Brooklyn change around them: factories became studios, old blocks became destinations, and the borough became a global symbol.</p>
      <p>Brooklynite exists to bring Brooklyn tradition forward through bridge shirts, Brooklyn baseball heritage caps, yellow taxi graphics, baby gifts, articles, events, and a community map that connects products back to place.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="bg-white py-14">
    <div class="container-shell grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
      {[
        ["Old Brooklyn / New Brooklyn", "The brand should carry memory without becoming stuck in nostalgia."],
        ["Family / Premium", "The shop stays warm and personal while the experience becomes sharper and more elevated."],
        ["Commerce / Community", "Products connect to stories, events, places, and future customer memories."]
      ].map(([title, copy]) => (
        <article class="rounded-lg border border-asphalt/10 bg-paper p-5">
          <h2 class="font-editorial text-2xl font-black text-asphalt">{title}</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 leading-7 text-ink/70">{copy}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
